notes: In the only Prudential Trophy match to be staged in Wales, Amiss continued his monopoly of centuries, reaching his second hundred off 116 balls in the 39th over.

milestones.description: Dennis Amiss has scored 2 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for ENG breaking John Edrich's record
Vic Pollard has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (38) in an innings in ODIs, going past Dennis Amiss's 36
Dennis Amiss has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (62) in an innings in ODIs, going past Dennis Amiss's 36
Vic Pollard has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (38) in an innings in ODIs for NZ, going past Hadlee's 16
Dennis Amiss has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (62) in an innings in ODIs for ENG, going past Dennis Amiss's 36
Geoff Boycott has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (5), going past Greg Chappell
Vic Pollard has become the top scorer for NZ in ODIs with 55 runs, going past Mark Burgess's 47
Hadlee has broken the record for most sixes (2) in ODIs, going past Mark Burgess's 1
Hadlee has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (2) in ODIs for NZ, going past Mark Burgess's 1
Vic Pollard's 55 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for NZ), surpassing Mark Burgess's 47
Alan Knott has broken the record for most dismissals (10) in ODIs, going past Rod Marsh's 7
Alan Knott has broken the record for most dismissals in an innings (4) in ODIs for ENG, going past Alan Knott's 3
Geoff Boycott has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (5) for ENG, going past D'Oliveira
Mark Burgess has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (2) for NZ, going past Collinge
Hadlee has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (2) in ODIs, going past Ian Chappell's 1
Constant has broken the record for officiating the most ODIs (2) as an umpire, going past Tom Brooks
Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss's 96-run partnership is the highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 76 between Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss
Vic Pollard and Glenn Turner's 55-run partnership is the highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 39 between Fletcher and Barry Wood
New Zealand's 158 is the lowest score in ODIs. They broke the earlier record of 165
Vic Pollard and Glenn Turner's 55-run partnership is NZ's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 45 between Ken Wadsworth and Mark Burgess
Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss's 96-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 76 between Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss
Dennis Amiss and Frank Hayes's 38-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 37 between John Edrich and D'Oliveira
Hastings and Glenn Turner's 5-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 2 between Hastings and Peter Coman
Vic Pollard and Glenn Turner's 55-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 36 between Graham Vivian and Mark Burgess
Vic Pollard and Bruce Taylor's 27-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 9 between Dayle Hadlee and Ken Wadsworth
Bruce Taylor and Hadlee's 25-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 8 between Ken Wadsworth and Hadlee
Howarth and Hadlee's 14-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 11 between Collinge and Hadlee
